@startuml create-game-sequence
!theme plain

title GDE Website — Sequence Diagram: Create Game Workflow

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #333333
  ActorBorderColor #333333
  LifeLineBorderColor #666666
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
  ParticipantBorderColor #333333
  NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  NoteBorderColor #FBC02D
  FontSize 12
}

actor "User" as User
participant "Browser\n(React SPA)" as Browser
participant "Nginx\n(Reverse Proxy)" as Nginx
participant "GamesController\n(Spring Boot)" as GamesCtrl
participant "JwtFilter\n(Security)" as JwtFilter
participant "JwtUtils\n(Token)" as JwtUtils
participant "GamesService\n(Business Logic)" as GamesSvc
participant "GamesRepository\n(JPA)" as GamesRepo
database "PostgreSQL" as Postgres

== 1. User navigates to Create Game page ==

User -> Browser : Clicks "Create Game" button
Browser -> Browser : ProtectedRoute checks AuthContext\nfor valid JWT token

note right of Browser
  If no token → redirect to /auth
  If token exists → render CreateGamePage
end note

== 2. User fills in game details and submits ==

User -> Browser : Fills title, description,\nbanner URL, tags\nand clicks "Submit"
Browser -> Browser : Validates form fields

== 3. Frontend sends authenticated POST request ==

Browser -> Nginx : POST /api/games\n{title, description, bannerUrl, tags}\nAuthorization: Bearer <JWT>
Nginx -> GamesCtrl : proxy_pass → POST /games\n(forwards Authorization header)

== 4. Backend validates JWT token ==

GamesCtrl -> JwtFilter : Filter chain intercepts request
JwtFilter -> JwtUtils : Validate JWT token
JwtUtils --> JwtFilter : Token valid → extract userId
JwtFilter --> GamesCtrl : Set Authentication principal\n(userId)

== 5. Backend processes game creation ==

GamesCtrl -> GamesCtrl : Check authentication\n(if null → 401 UNAUTHORIZED)
GamesCtrl -> GamesSvc : createGame(request, userId)

== 6. Service layer creates game entity ==

GamesSvc -> GamesRepo : Save GamesEntity\n(title, description, bannerUrl,\nauthorId, timestamps)
GamesRepo -> Postgres : INSERT INTO games\n(title, description, banner_url,\nauthor_id, created_at, updated_at)
Postgres --> GamesRepo : Game saved (with generated ID)

== 7. Service handles tags ==

GamesSvc -> GamesSvc : Resolve tag names\n→ TagEntity references
GamesSvc -> GamesRepo : Save GameTagEntity\n(game_id, tag_id)
GamesRepo -> Postgres : INSERT INTO game_tags\n(game_id, tag_id)
Postgres --> GamesRepo : Tags linked

== 8. Response flows back ==

GamesSvc --> GamesCtrl : Games entity (with ID)
GamesCtrl --> Nginx : HTTP 201 Created\n{game data}
Nginx --> Browser : HTTP 201 Created\n{game data}

== 9. Frontend updates UI ==

Browser -> Browser : Update state with\nnew game data
Browser --> User : Show success message\n/ redirect to game page

note over User, Postgres
  **Key architecture decisions demonstrated:**
  1. Stateless JWT authentication (no server-side sessions)
  2. Nginx reverse proxy for frontend-backend communication
  3. Service layer pattern (Controller → Service → Repository)
  4. JPA/Hibernate ORM with PostgreSQL
  5. Tag-based game categorization via join table
end note

@enduml